"{\n  \"text\": \"Hi everybody, I want to make a quick video about die-off symptoms. When you have an unbalanced gut, an extremely unbalanced gut, when you know you're having a little bit of an issue, jumping into fermented foods because you hear it's gut healthy might be too extreme a first step. A lot of times a better first step is small amounts of raw fruits and vegetables with your food, with your meals, uh, and bone broth. Sometimes fermented foods can be too fast acting, too powerful, because fermented foods, the bacteria in them will hunt down the pathogenic or bad bacteria in your gut and kill it off in too great an abundance too quickly. As this bacteria dies, it releases toxins, which can get you gassy, which can get you bloated, make you uncomfortable, even sometimes make you sick. So, as a first step, don't jump to fermented foods, bridge to fermented foods after working with an improved diet and lessened sugars over a couple weeks. Anyway, thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hi everybody, I want to make a quick video about die-off symptoms.\",\n      \"start\": 0.4,\n      \"end\": 4.08,\n      \"duration\": 3.68,\n      \"confidence\": 0.99,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" Hi\",\n          \"start\": 0.4,\n          \"end\": 0.72,\n          \"duration\": 0.32,\n          \"confidence\": 0.997\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.8,\n          \"end\": 0.96,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.96,\n          \"end\": 1.12,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.12,\n          \"end\": 1.28,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \",\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.36,\n    